/datum/faith/old_god
	name = "Genesism"
	desc = "   </br>''There is only ONE.'' </br>  </br>After the Bloodwake, Psydon fell silent. Most had feared that He had undertaken the ultimate sacrifice to save this world from the Archdaemons' rampage, and - in the midst of mourning - turned their prayers to lesser gods. Yet, throughout the centuries, there always remained those who kept faith in Psydon above all else: be it in one way, or another- the Valorians. </br>  </br>Amongst the countless denominations that're peppered across Valorian lands, the Orthodoxy is the most widely-practiced: formed within the territories that make it up and made infamous through holy warfare. </br>  </br>The Orthodoxists believe that Psydon still lives, and is soon destined to return. Unanswered prayers and faltering miracles are merely tests of faith, nothing more. While the Pantheon's Gods might be widely praised, they are still nothing before Him: and as such, they are not the true divine. If cultists refuse to convert, then they must be destroyed. </br>  </br>With the world's end upon the horizon, however, even Psydon's most faithful worshippers - no matter the denomination - are facing a crisis like no other.</br>  </br>Time is running out. Lowly fool, sacrificial hero, blessed idiot, holy lamb: will you endure as He had, in order to save this world from damnation? Or will you shepherd its end, so that something greater might rise from the ashes?"
	worshippers = "Traditionalists, Spiritualists, Accelerationists, and the Hopeful."
	godhead = /datum/patron/old_god
